{# 
    Table Row (<tr>)
    ===========================================================================

    Defines a row in a table.

    Variables:
    - `tr_content`: The content inside the <tr> element, typically table cells
      (<td> or <th>). Defaults to a single default cell.
    - `tr_class`: The class attribute for the <tr> element. Defaults to "default-class".
    - `tr_id`: The id attribute for the <tr> element. Defaults to "default-id".
    - `tr_style`: The style attribute for the <tr> element. Defaults to "".

    Notes:
    - The `| safe` filter is used to include HTML content safely.
    - The <tr> element is used to define a row in an HTML table.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/tr
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_tr.asp

#}

<tr 
    class="{{ tr_class | default('default-class') | e }}" 
    id="{{ tr_id | default('default-id') | e }}" 
    style="{{ tr_style | default('') | e }}"
>
    {{ tr_content | default('<td>Default cell content</td>') | safe }}
</tr>
